[SN]TITLE[SN]
US stocks end higher but Twitter tumbles

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
US stocks closed higher on Monday, with oil firms boosting the Dow Jones index, as crude prices rose.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Exxon was the biggest riser on the index, adding 2%, while Chevron rose 1.9%, as US crude prices jumped 3% to $51.35 a barrel, a one-year high.
But shares in Twitter tumbled 11.5% after reports that more bidders had lost interest in a takeover bid.
Bloomberg said that Google, Walt Disney and Salesforce were now unlikely to make an offer.
The social media site is said to be considering a takeover deal amid concerns over its growth.
Overall, the Dow Jones Industrial Average ended up 0.5% at 18,329.
The tech-heavy Nasdaq gained 0.7% to 5,328.67, while the S&P 500 rose 0.5% to 2,163.66.
Shares in Apple gained as the woes for its rival Samsung intensified. Phone companies in the US and the UK have now suspended replacements of its latest Note 7 device amid reports that new "safe" models are still at risk of catching fire.
Apple shares rose 1.8% to $116.59.
